      • Serialized Fields

        • serviceName

          String serviceName
          for documentation. Not used as part of any logic.

        • userId

          Value userId
          user for whom this is created. Useful in security check, populating relevant fields in db, as well as logging.

        • fields

          Map<K,V> fields
          this has name-object pairs, and not restricted to name-Value pairs. designed to carry any data object across layers

        • payLoad

          String payLoad
          could be request/response depending on direction. As of now this is JSON flowing between client and server. We should be able to use any other serialized data representations like XML

        • messages

          List<E> messages
          presence indicates error from server

        • nbrErrors

          int nbrErrors
          tracked based on messages added

        • executionTime

          int executionTime
          ms taken by server to execute service. does not include latency in getting the service etc..

        • cacheForInput

          String[] cacheForInput
          output data is cachable for this comma separated list of input field values. Null implies that this can not be cached. empty string means it can be used for all users irrespective of input data. If this is userId specific, then _userId would be the first field.

        • cacheKey

          String cacheKey

        • messageBox

          MessageBox messageBox
          used in the input as mechanism to pass message bewteen the caller and a service

        • sessionFields

          Map<K,V> sessionFields
          session fields
